Without manifest cause no one was to presume to pronounce against them sentence of interdict or excommunication. All customs and ancient liberties and immunities were permanently sanctioned. The enclosures of their houses and granges were protected by apostolical authority from theft and arson, and had the privilege of freedom from arrest.
